# Agentic Customer Operations — Diagnostic Starter

This repo generates three diagnostic products for McKinsey client engagements. Each produces a deployable Vercel web app.

## Products

1. **NRR Diagnostic (Basic)** — NRR benchmark + customer journey map + diagnostic synthesis (~15-30 min)
2. **NRR Diagnostic (Enhanced)** — Full deep-dive with maturity assessment, waterfall, value-at-stake, and actions (~15-30 min)
3. **Customer Operations Assessment** — AI readiness assessment for CS, PS, Support with role-by-role analysis (~15-30 min)

## Gold Standard Examples

- Basic: https://nrr-cx-okta.vercel.app/
- Enhanced: https://nrr-cx-databricks-enhanced.vercel.app/
- Assessment: https://oracle-ops-assessment.vercel.app/

## How to Generate

Tell Cursor one of:
- "Generate an NRR diagnostic basic for [Company]"
- "Generate an NRR diagnostic enhanced for [Company]"
- "Generate a customer operations assessment for [Company]"

Cursor will follow the rules in `.cursor/rules/` for the chosen product type.

## Naming Convention

- `nrr-cx-{client}-basic` or `nrr-cx-{client}-enhanced` for NRR diagnostics
- `{client}-ops-assessment` for customer operations assessments
- Client names: lowercase, hyphens OK (e.g., `databricks`, `t-mobile`)

## Templates

- `templates/basic/` — Next.js static site template for Basic NRR diagnostic
- `templates/enhanced/` — Next.js static site template for Enhanced NRR diagnostic
- `templates/assessment/` — Vite + React frontend + Python agent backend for Customer Ops Assessment

## After Generation

1. Review the output for accuracy
2. Deploy: `./scripts/deploy.sh {client} {product}`
3. The deploy script auto-updates `diagnostics.json` and pushes to the portal

## Tech Stack

**NRR Diagnostics (Basic + Enhanced):**
- Next.js 16 + React 19 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS 4 + Recharts
- Static export for Vercel deployment
- All data in `public/data/client-data.json`

**Customer Operations Assessment:**
- Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind (frontend)
- FastAPI + Python agent framework (backend)
- Assessment data in `ui/public/assessment.json`
- Reference data per company in `reference/`

## Key Rules

- Never hardcode client names in component code
- Follow the quality checklist before deploying (see `.cursor/rules/`)
- Real verbatim quotes only — never generate fake customer quotes
- Deploy script auto-syncs to the portal at https://portal-agentic-customer.vercel.app
